cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the capacity-achieving communication scheme over various channels, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of the communication scheme over different channels, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the performance of spatial coupling, which is a technique used in social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of Hadamard-based encoders, which are commonly used in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the analysis tools used to evaluate the performance of the communication scheme, which may involve computational complexity.
